WEBVTT

00:04.655 --> 00:07.931
♪♪

00:07.931 --> 00:11.413
♪♪

00:11.413 --> 00:15.310
[ Laughing ]

00:15.310 --> 00:18.758
I mean, given how many times
you just said it,

00:18.758 --> 00:22.551
I would think you'd know that
Belle is actually my lastname.

00:22.551 --> 00:24.724
I go by T.R.

00:24.724 --> 00:26.172
[Russian accent] I know.

00:26.172 --> 00:29.137
But "T.R." doesn't roll off
the tongue as well.

00:29.137 --> 00:31.103
[ Chuckles ]

00:31.103 --> 00:32.862
Well, then...

00:32.862 --> 00:37.862
maybe you just need
a little more practice.

00:37.862 --> 00:38.931
Maybe I do.

00:38.931 --> 00:40.068
[ Glasses clink ]

00:40.068 --> 00:47.206
♪♪

00:47.206 --> 00:49.103
[ Exhales heavily ]

00:49.103 --> 00:54.275
♪♪

00:54.275 --> 00:56.551
[ Message bloops ]

00:56.551 --> 00:59.655
Help! Help!
He's passed out!

00:59.655 --> 01:01.620
He's...

01:01.620 --> 01:04.034
♪♪

01:04.034 --> 01:06.068
I don't know
what happened.

01:06.068 --> 01:08.551
♪♪

01:13.206 --> 01:14.896
[ Siren wails ]

01:14.896 --> 01:20.206
♪♪

01:20.206 --> 01:22.724
[ Man speaking Russian ]

01:22.724 --> 01:27.758
♪♪

01:27.758 --> 01:32.620
♪♪

01:32.620 --> 01:34.655
He's been bitten
by a fat-tail scorpion.[ Gasps ]

01:34.655 --> 01:36.620
We need to get him
to a hospital immediately.

01:36.620 --> 01:37.931
Yes. Yeah.

01:37.931 --> 01:46.068
♪♪

01:46.068 --> 01:48.103
Wait! I -- I want
to go with him!

01:48.103 --> 01:51.723
♪♪

01:59.068 --> 02:00.758
[ Weapons cocking ]

02:02.655 --> 02:06.241
You really thought
you could get away with this?

02:06.241 --> 02:07.379
Yeah, we kinda did.

02:07.379 --> 02:09.448
Yeah, felt like
a good plan.

02:09.448 --> 02:12.137
You know why?
'Cause we brought backup.

02:13.482 --> 02:15.689
I thought you said
this was gonna be hard.

02:17.310 --> 02:18.896
You boys
are in trouble now.

02:18.896 --> 02:22.034
You doknow why they call
that brother the White Knight?

02:22.034 --> 02:24.896
♪♪

02:24.896 --> 02:27.275
[ Thunder rumbles ]

02:27.275 --> 02:31.068
♪♪

02:31.068 --> 02:33.137
[ Zapping ]Aah!

02:33.137 --> 02:35.275
[ Men screaming ]

02:35.275 --> 02:42.862
♪♪

02:42.862 --> 02:46.862
No, no, no, no!
H-Hold up. Jin, hold up.

02:46.862 --> 02:48.620
That's not how
the story goes.

02:48.620 --> 02:50.965
It's called creative license,
Magnum.

02:50.965 --> 02:53.344
You try keeping the attention
of a 6-month-old baby

02:53.344 --> 02:55.448
using a book
with no pictures.

02:55.448 --> 02:58.137
Have you ever read a book
with no pictures?

02:58.137 --> 03:00.068
Of course I have.
That's so rude.

03:00.068 --> 03:01.413
Do menus count?

03:01.413 --> 03:02.793
Rick:
Uh, Jin, I'm pretty sure

03:02.793 --> 03:04.448
giving the White Knight
superpowers

03:04.448 --> 03:06.034
is not something
that Robin would do.

03:06.034 --> 03:08.413
Maybe it's something
he shoulddo. For his next book.

03:08.413 --> 03:10.724
I don't know.
Joy didseem entertained.

03:10.724 --> 03:12.724
Rick: Yeah, thanks
for doing my job for me.

03:12.724 --> 03:14.655
I gotta get her back
to Suzy's place, though.

03:14.655 --> 03:17.655
Hey, uh, Kumu said we should
stagger our visits to TC

03:17.655 --> 03:19.827
so it's not so chaotic
on the first day.

03:19.827 --> 03:21.896
Said she'll text us
when it's cool to swing by.

03:21.896 --> 03:23.103
Mm.

03:23.103 --> 03:24.655
Hey, Magnum, speaking of
Robin's book...

03:24.655 --> 03:27.413
would you mind if you
passed this along to him?

03:27.413 --> 03:29.241
[ Chuckles ]

03:29.241 --> 03:32.206
[ Laughs ] Hey, Rick.
Check it out.

03:33.655 --> 03:35.448
-Jin.
-Ha ha. What?

03:35.448 --> 03:36.930
Jin, you don't have muscles
like that.

03:36.930 --> 03:39.862
Yes, I do. They're hidden
under my winter layer.

03:39.862 --> 03:42.448
Uh-huh. And -- And --
And what exactly is this?

03:42.448 --> 03:44.655
It's my pitch for
Robin's next series.

03:44.655 --> 03:46.413
Alright? It's the cover
of the first book.

03:46.413 --> 03:47.689
What's it about?I don't know.

03:47.689 --> 03:49.067
That's why
Robin's involved.

03:49.067 --> 03:50.517
You don't know anything
about writing!

03:50.517 --> 03:52.103
Okay. Thanks, Jin.

03:52.103 --> 03:54.827
You create a cool cover, and
you work backwards from there.

03:54.827 --> 03:58.000
No, no, that's not how it works.
But I gotta meet a client.

03:58.000 --> 04:00.586
Uh, I will, however,
give this to Robin.

04:00.586 --> 04:02.724
-You think he'll do it?
-Uh, no. No.

04:02.724 --> 04:04.206
But, uh, he knows
a lot about you,

04:04.206 --> 04:06.758
and I think he's gonna
get a kick out of this.

04:08.758 --> 04:11.517
Millie: The VA has
social services, primary care,

04:11.517 --> 04:14.206
a mental-health center,
and our own pharmacy.

04:14.206 --> 04:16.654
You'll split most of your time
between physical therapy

04:16.654 --> 04:18.344
and the residential wing.

04:18.344 --> 04:23.724
♪♪

04:23.724 --> 04:28.931
♪♪

04:28.931 --> 04:30.344
Hey. Not too shabby.

04:30.344 --> 04:32.758
Kumu: Mm.
It's quite spacious.

04:32.758 --> 04:34.655
Millie: It's only been 12 days
since your injury,

04:34.655 --> 04:36.586
so you'll ease into things
with stretches

04:36.586 --> 04:39.586
and occupational therapy
tomorrow, then hit PT hard.

04:39.586 --> 04:41.448
We've got a great staff
who can assist you

04:41.448 --> 04:42.862
with specific tasks

04:42.862 --> 04:45.137
or just getting from
your chair to your bed.

04:45.137 --> 04:49.482
Millie, he can bench more
than most people can squat.

04:49.482 --> 04:51.448
He'll be fine
with a slide board.

04:51.448 --> 04:53.137
Yeah, I was thinking
the slide board.

04:53.137 --> 04:54.551
What's a slide board?

04:54.551 --> 04:56.586
It's a technique
using this board

04:56.586 --> 04:58.551
to move from your chair

04:58.551 --> 05:02.896
to your bed,
bench, toilet.

05:02.896 --> 05:04.379
Hm.

05:05.689 --> 05:08.068
What's that
pizza-cutter-lookin' thing?

05:08.068 --> 05:11.586
Oh, it's a pinwheel.
Tests reflexes and sensation.

05:11.586 --> 05:13.896
To see if feeling's coming
back into your legs.

05:13.896 --> 05:16.586
Well, let's try.
Just for the hell of it.

05:24.379 --> 05:25.965
Kumu: Anything?

05:28.241 --> 05:30.551
Nah.

05:30.551 --> 05:32.310
Worth a shot, though.

05:32.310 --> 05:38.310
♪♪

05:38.310 --> 05:41.758
♪ I turn on my radio ♪

05:41.758 --> 05:44.724
♪♪

05:44.724 --> 05:47.724
♪ Sweet Hawaiian music ♪

05:47.724 --> 05:50.931
♪ You know that
sweet Hawaiian music ♪

05:50.931 --> 05:53.689
Higgins: Hey.
Sorry I'm late.

05:53.689 --> 05:56.758
It's alright.
Client's not even here.

05:56.758 --> 05:59.586
I still don't know why we
had to take separate cars.

05:59.586 --> 06:01.379
Told you.
Something came up.

06:01.379 --> 06:03.482
Yeah, but...

06:03.482 --> 06:05.758
I don't know.
You're being so vague about it.

06:05.758 --> 06:07.103
You really want to know?

06:07.103 --> 06:09.310
Well, yeah, you're making
a thing out of it,

06:09.310 --> 06:11.275
so I kinda do
want to know.

06:11.275 --> 06:13.586
Very well.

06:13.586 --> 06:15.310
I'm late.

06:15.310 --> 06:16.689
I understand
that you're late,

06:16.689 --> 06:18.448
but I want to know
whyyou're late.

06:18.448 --> 06:20.275
No, Thomas.

06:20.275 --> 06:23.000
I'm, uh --
I'm...late.

06:26.551 --> 06:27.827
Oh, okay.

06:27.827 --> 06:29.482
It's probably
a false alarm,

06:29.482 --> 06:32.000
but over-the-counter pregnancy
tests just aren't reliable,

06:32.000 --> 06:33.862
so I thought
I'd pop by my physician

06:33.862 --> 06:35.448
just to get a blood test.

06:35.448 --> 06:37.862
Well, that's great.

06:37.862 --> 06:41.206
That -- You know,
great that you're, uh...

06:41.206 --> 06:42.586
getting tested.

06:42.586 --> 06:44.034
Not great that
you're not pregnant.

06:44.034 --> 06:46.586
Not that being pregnant
wouldn't be great, just --

06:46.586 --> 06:48.413
[ Chuckles ]
That's a lot of "greats."

06:48.413 --> 06:50.517
[ Cellphone rings ]

06:51.482 --> 06:53.172
It's not me.

06:53.172 --> 06:54.310
[ Cellphone rings ]

06:54.310 --> 06:57.172
It's not me, either.

06:57.172 --> 06:59.000
[ Cellphone rings ]

07:01.413 --> 07:04.241
[ Cellphone rings ]

07:04.241 --> 07:05.758
[ Beep ]
Hello?

07:05.758 --> 07:07.827
Man: Thomas, Juliet.
Thank you showing up.

07:07.827 --> 07:09.724
This is your client, Xavier.

07:09.724 --> 07:12.482
Sorry about the theatrics,
but I wish to remain anonymous.

07:12.482 --> 07:15.068
And why is that? Because of the nature
of this case.

07:15.068 --> 07:17.517
I have information that
someone has taken out a hit

07:17.517 --> 07:19.586
on a 12-year-old girl.

07:19.586 --> 07:20.931
I want you to find
who ordered it.

07:20.931 --> 07:23.137
Well, how do you
even know about this?

07:23.137 --> 07:25.344
Because I'm the hitman
they hired.

07:25.344 --> 07:33.275
♪♪

07:33.275 --> 07:41.206
♪♪

07:41.206 --> 07:48.965
♪♪

07:48.965 --> 07:50.862
Xavier, we normally
deal with clients

07:50.862 --> 07:52.310
on the right side
of the law.

07:52.310 --> 07:57.068
Um, contract killers don't
really fit into that category.

07:57.068 --> 07:59.275
You can say what you want
about my profession,

07:59.275 --> 08:01.655
but even I have limits.
I'd never kill a kid.

08:01.655 --> 08:03.931
Well, that's very noble
of you.

08:03.931 --> 08:05.758
And not that
we doubt you,

08:05.758 --> 08:08.137
but we would appreciate
a few more specifics.

08:08.137 --> 08:10.000
The person who ordered
the hit contacted me

08:10.000 --> 08:12.000
anonymously
through the Dark Web.

08:12.000 --> 08:13.689
What engine
and what directory?

08:13.689 --> 08:15.206
I browse through Whonix.

08:15.206 --> 08:17.689
Clients contact me
through Dread.

08:17.689 --> 08:19.103
[ Beep ]That legit?

08:19.103 --> 08:20.379
Yeah.
[ Beep ]

08:20.379 --> 08:22.413
This is an honest conversation,
Thomas.

08:22.413 --> 08:24.000
No need to mute yourself.

08:25.827 --> 08:28.068
And quit looking around.
You won't find me.

08:28.068 --> 08:30.206
You got a weapon
trained on us?

08:30.206 --> 08:33.965
No. I just wish
to protect my anonymity.

08:33.965 --> 08:37.379
I'm not gonna kill you
even if you decide to walk away.

08:37.379 --> 08:38.965
That's very gracious
of you.

08:38.965 --> 08:40.724
Besides, I already know
that you're gonna help me.

08:40.724 --> 08:43.309
And why is that? Because after
I turned down this job,

08:43.309 --> 08:45.068
I realized that
whoever tried to hire me

08:45.068 --> 08:47.275
would just hire someone else
to carry out the hit.

08:47.275 --> 08:50.103
So if you turn down this case,
an innocent girl will die.

08:50.103 --> 08:52.482
And I don't think
you're the kind of people

08:52.482 --> 08:53.689
that will let that happen.

08:53.689 --> 08:55.344
You're right.
Continue.

08:55.344 --> 08:57.620
The girl is currently in hiding.
I don't know where.

08:57.620 --> 08:59.034
But everything I have on her,

08:59.034 --> 09:00.689
along with my screen-grabs
and correspondence

09:00.689 --> 09:02.793
with the client are on the
phone that you're holding.

09:02.793 --> 09:04.310
And we can contact you
at this number?

09:04.310 --> 09:07.068
No. After this call,
you'll never hear from me again.

09:07.068 --> 09:09.827
I've done my part.
Now you do yours.

09:09.827 --> 09:11.862
Good luck.[ Beep ]

09:17.724 --> 09:21.896
♪♪

09:21.896 --> 09:26.827
♪ Yeah-ah-ah-ah ♪

09:26.827 --> 09:31.137
♪ Yeah-ah-ah-ah ♪

09:31.137 --> 09:35.965
♪ Hey, Good times come,
and good times go ♪

09:35.965 --> 09:38.137
♪ I'd only wish
the good times ♪

09:38.137 --> 09:41.172
♪ Would last a little longer ♪

09:41.172 --> 09:44.172
♪ I think about
the good times we had ♪

09:44.172 --> 09:46.862
♪ And why we had to end them ♪

09:46.862 --> 09:48.965
♪ Oh, oh-oh ♪

09:48.965 --> 09:54.241
♪ The story of my life ♪

09:54.241 --> 09:55.413
♪♪

09:55.413 --> 09:59.965
♪ Yeah-ah-ah-ah ♪

09:59.965 --> 10:04.793
♪ Yeah-ah-ah-ah♪

10:04.793 --> 10:07.827
♪ La-la-la-la♪

10:07.827 --> 10:11.275
♪ Story of my life♪

10:11.275 --> 10:13.689
Is that yours,
or do you clean boats?

10:13.689 --> 10:15.931
[ Chuckles ]
No. Neither. No.

10:15.931 --> 10:17.896
Uh, actually,
I live here.

10:17.896 --> 10:20.103
I could tell.
You missed a spot.

10:20.103 --> 10:21.827
Oh, yeah?
Yeah.

10:21.827 --> 10:23.896
Well, I'm not a pro.

10:24.793 --> 10:26.551
Yeah, name's Rick.

10:26.551 --> 10:28.068
Piper.

10:28.068 --> 10:29.896
Checkin' to see
if you're the competish'.

10:29.896 --> 10:31.724
Ohh.
I clean
a lot of boats here.

10:31.724 --> 10:34.551
Really? Haven't see you
at La Mariana.

10:34.551 --> 10:36.137
I never go to that dump.

10:36.137 --> 10:37.689
Oof.
Uh-oh.

10:37.689 --> 10:39.137
Ouch.
You work there?

10:39.137 --> 10:41.620
Worse.
You're the manager?

10:41.620 --> 10:43.862
Ugh! Worse!

10:43.862 --> 10:45.551
I own it.

10:45.551 --> 10:46.862
Oh.

10:46.862 --> 10:48.206
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

10:48.206 --> 10:49.344
I'm sorry.

10:49.344 --> 10:50.931
[ Laughs ]

10:50.931 --> 10:54.172
Um, okay, calling it a dump
was a little harsh, but, um...

10:54.172 --> 10:55.689
Alright.

10:55.689 --> 10:58.310
You ever love something so much
that you gorged on it

10:58.310 --> 11:00.448
then you got super sick
and you never ate it again?

11:00.448 --> 11:03.034
Well, that was Mai Tais.

11:03.034 --> 11:05.586
For me, it's your bar.
Had a week-long hangover.

11:05.586 --> 11:07.655
Oh.
Never went back.

11:07.655 --> 11:09.827
Oh.
Well, when was that?

11:09.827 --> 11:12.862
Uh, 25th birthday.
About 7 years ago.

11:12.862 --> 11:15.241
To be fair, that was before
I took the place over,

11:15.241 --> 11:18.275
and since then, I've revamped
the drink menu and other things.

11:18.275 --> 11:20.689
You should come by
and give it a shot.

11:20.689 --> 11:22.310
Let me think about it.

11:22.310 --> 11:23.862
Okay.

11:23.862 --> 11:25.758
Nah. I'm good.

11:25.758 --> 11:27.344
[ Chuckles ]
Thanks, though.

11:27.344 --> 11:28.862
It was nice
to meet you, Rick.

11:28.862 --> 11:30.655
Nice to meet you.

11:30.655 --> 11:37.827
♪♪

11:37.827 --> 11:40.689
Okay, the files
that Xavier sent us

11:40.689 --> 11:43.310
should be uploaded
shortly.

11:43.310 --> 11:46.586
So, uh...
how you feeling?

11:46.586 --> 11:47.551
Huh? You feel good?

11:47.551 --> 11:49.551
Do I feel good?

11:49.551 --> 11:51.172
Yeah.
Just, like, in general.

11:51.172 --> 11:54.827
Do you feel maybe more pregnant,
less pregnant than this morning?

11:54.827 --> 11:57.620
Uh, I feel the exact same amount
of pregnant as I did earlier.

11:57.620 --> 12:01.448
Actually, um, I think
the test results are in.

12:01.448 --> 12:03.000
Oh, they're --
the results are in,

12:03.000 --> 12:04.655
but you chose
not to tell me?

12:04.655 --> 12:06.482
No, I just missed a call from
the doctor, like, just now,

12:06.482 --> 12:09.206
and clearly, I have not had time
to call her back.

12:09.206 --> 12:12.517
This case is more important.
If I am not pregnant now,

12:12.517 --> 12:14.137
I'll still be not pregnant
tomorrow.

12:14.137 --> 12:15.517
Yeah, but if you are
pregnant now,

12:15.517 --> 12:18.551
you will be
more pregnant tomorrow.

12:18.551 --> 12:22.620
I feel like I'm detecting both
notes of excitement and worry,

12:22.620 --> 12:26.344
so I guess you're thinking about
what this might mean for us.

12:26.344 --> 12:28.275
Yeah, yeah.
I-It's all of that.

12:28.275 --> 12:31.034
[ Beeping]Oh!

12:31.034 --> 12:32.517
What do we got?Okay.

12:32.517 --> 12:35.172
Looks like we've got
a selection of screen-grabs

12:35.172 --> 12:39.379
of Xavier's encrypted
correspondence with his client.

12:39.379 --> 12:42.344
Folder marked "Anna."
What about that?

12:42.344 --> 12:44.310
Anna Park. 12 years old
from Kapolei.

12:44.310 --> 12:46.206
There's nothing in here
to indicate

12:46.206 --> 12:47.862
why anyone would want
to target her.

12:47.862 --> 12:49.758
Well, clearly,
they see her as a threat.

12:49.758 --> 12:53.413
She could maybe I.D. somebody
or she was witness to a crime.

12:53.413 --> 12:55.724
Oh, okay. I've got a record
for her in DCFS.

12:55.724 --> 12:58.586
No father to speak of.
She was raised by a single mom,

12:58.586 --> 13:02.344
who recently passed away
from an autoimmune disease.

13:02.344 --> 13:03.965
Look.
She goes to St. Andrew's.

13:03.965 --> 13:06.413
That's one of the boarding
schools that Robin donates to.

13:06.413 --> 13:08.000
Well, that should
give us an in.

13:08.000 --> 13:10.034
I mean, if anybody's gonna
know where Anna's at,

13:10.034 --> 13:11.620
it's gonna be
one of her classmates.

13:11.620 --> 13:14.103
Yeah. Okay, uh, I'll call
the headmistress.

13:14.103 --> 13:16.310
And then I'll head over
to St. Andrew's.

13:16.310 --> 13:18.344
Alright. I'm gonna see if I can
find anything out on Anna

13:18.344 --> 13:20.620
from social services
and then circle back.

13:20.620 --> 13:22.275
Okay.

13:23.275 --> 13:25.000
Shammy: Okay. You make sure
your wheels are locked

13:25.000 --> 13:27.344
and your footrests are up,
then you make sure this board

13:27.344 --> 13:30.793
is wedged properly on the seat
and on the bed, alright?

13:30.793 --> 13:34.551
Then, with your arms, obviously,
you're just gonna shimmy.

13:34.551 --> 13:38.068
Just gonna shimmy. Right?
Right up the board. Okay?

13:38.068 --> 13:40.206
Up, up, and over.

13:40.206 --> 13:42.275
And you're on the bed,
just like...that.

13:42.275 --> 13:43.965
It's just that simple.

13:43.965 --> 13:45.482
Shammy,
you make it look easy.

13:45.482 --> 13:47.793
'Cause I had to do it
about a million times

13:47.793 --> 13:49.275
after my own injury.

13:49.275 --> 13:51.413
So, what do you say,
big guy?

13:51.413 --> 13:53.206
Want to try?

13:53.206 --> 13:55.689
Maybe later. I'm -- I'm
still getting settled in.

13:55.689 --> 13:58.586
That's totally --Come on, TC. You got this.

13:58.586 --> 14:01.034
Look, I know how you feel
right now,

14:01.034 --> 14:04.896
but trust me, this is the most
important time to push yourself.

14:04.896 --> 14:09.793
♪♪

14:09.793 --> 14:11.620
Alright. [ Sighs ]

14:14.827 --> 14:17.482
There you go.
There you go.

14:19.310 --> 14:22.172
Oh, yeah, by the way,
you gotta take the arm rest off.

14:28.413 --> 14:31.034
Higgins: So, I know that Anna's
been missing for a few days now.

14:31.034 --> 14:33.172
Have you reported it
to HPD?

14:33.172 --> 14:36.758
We did -- the first four times
she disappeared.

14:36.758 --> 14:39.275
She's had a rough time
since her mom passed,

14:39.275 --> 14:41.206
and running away is how
she's dealt with things,

14:41.206 --> 14:42.965
but she always comes back
after a few days,

14:42.965 --> 14:45.275
so we haven't been
so concerned.

14:45.275 --> 14:46.965
Is this time different?

14:46.965 --> 14:48.482
I'm not sure yet,

14:48.482 --> 14:50.965
but it would be helpful to talk
to some of Anna's friends.

14:50.965 --> 14:53.965
Well, she doesn't have many,
but she isclose to her teacher,

14:53.965 --> 14:55.241
Margaret Neely.

14:55.241 --> 14:57.000
Margaret was friends
with Anna's mom.

14:57.000 --> 14:58.344
After she passed away,

14:58.344 --> 15:00.586
Anna started going to her
for guidance.

15:00.586 --> 15:04.172
Okay. May I speak
with Margaret?

15:05.172 --> 15:07.275
She's actually
not here today.

15:07.275 --> 15:09.827
She didn't call in,
which is unlike her.

15:09.827 --> 15:12.896
I didn't think anything of it
till now.

15:12.896 --> 15:14.482
So, first,
Anna goes missing,

15:14.482 --> 15:16.034
having just been
marked for death,

15:16.034 --> 15:19.206
and then the person she trusts
most in the world is now MIA.

15:19.206 --> 15:21.000
It's got to be connected.[ Line ringing]

15:21.000 --> 15:23.275
Margaret: You have reached
the voicemail box of Margaret.

15:23.275 --> 15:25.965
Margaret's phone is still
going straight to voicemail.

15:25.965 --> 15:34.758
♪♪

15:34.758 --> 15:35.827
What is it?

15:35.827 --> 15:38.000
The, uh, key hole.

15:39.862 --> 15:41.724
Fresh marks.
Someone was just here.

15:41.724 --> 15:44.689
Yeah, or still is.
You want to go around back?

15:44.689 --> 15:45.862
Yeah.

15:45.862 --> 15:52.965
♪♪

15:52.965 --> 16:00.034
♪♪

16:00.034 --> 16:01.413
Hey.

16:01.413 --> 16:02.793
Oh, my God!
Please don't shoot!

16:02.793 --> 16:04.482
Who are you
What are you doing here?

16:04.482 --> 16:06.344
I'm a regional sales rep
for Midas Solar.

16:06.344 --> 16:07.724
I-I don't want
any trouble.

16:07.724 --> 16:10.379
I heard another voice.
Who you talking to?

16:10.379 --> 16:11.793
It's -- It's my partner.

16:11.793 --> 16:13.827
She's right outside.
She'll be back in a second.

16:13.827 --> 16:15.586
Hi! Oh, my God!

16:15.586 --> 16:23.517
♪♪

16:23.517 --> 16:31.275
♪♪

16:31.275 --> 16:34.000
[ Engine starts ]

16:34.000 --> 16:35.896
[ Tires squeal,
vehicle departs ]

16:35.896 --> 16:43.724
♪♪

16:43.724 --> 16:47.379
Well. I think we just met
Xavier's replacement.

16:47.379 --> 16:50.275
Yeah. Looks like he's
one step ahead of us.

16:54.206 --> 16:57.172
[ Police radio chatter ]

16:57.172 --> 16:58.586
Higgins: Any news
on Margaret Neely?

16:58.586 --> 17:00.275
Katsumoto: Yeah,
she's in the hospital --

17:00.275 --> 17:01.620
unconscious
with multiple fractures.

17:01.620 --> 17:03.275
According to a witness,
she was running down

17:03.275 --> 17:04.862
the middle of the street
in Waikiki this morning,

17:04.862 --> 17:07.137
looking over her shoulder, when
she was struck by a vehicle.

17:07.137 --> 17:09.517
Magnum: Anna must have told her
somebody was coming after her.

17:09.517 --> 17:10.827
Probably the same guy
we just met.

17:10.827 --> 17:12.586
I mean, he chased her,
she ran into the street,

17:12.586 --> 17:14.517
got hit by a car
before she can get help.

17:14.517 --> 17:16.655
Then he circled back here
to search her house.

17:16.655 --> 17:17.964
Care to fill me in?Alright.

17:17.964 --> 17:21.344
So, our client was hired
to kill Anna Park.

17:21.344 --> 17:22.896
She's a 12-year-old girl.

17:22.896 --> 17:25.964
Margaret Neely is her teacher
and informal guardian.

17:25.964 --> 17:28.655
We came here hoping that
Margaret could tell us
Anna's whereabouts.

17:28.655 --> 17:30.586
So you guys are working
with hitmen now?

17:30.586 --> 17:33.068
No, no, no.
He turned down the job, right?

17:33.068 --> 17:34.586
Then the man who hired him

17:34.586 --> 17:36.586
hired a second hitman
to go after her.

17:36.586 --> 17:38.517
Which is why
you took the case.

17:38.517 --> 17:40.827
Any idea who
this second hitman is?

17:40.827 --> 17:44.172
Well, no, but...

17:44.172 --> 17:46.517
hopefully we will soon.

17:46.517 --> 17:49.310
That's one way
to collect DNA.

17:49.310 --> 17:50.724
I'll have the lab
test the blood

17:50.724 --> 17:53.620
and make sure they get
the ring back to you.

17:53.620 --> 17:55.551
So long as you share
what you found in this house.

17:55.551 --> 17:57.172
How do you know
we found anything?

17:57.172 --> 17:59.379
'Cause I know you. You guys
were here a good 20 minutes

17:59.379 --> 18:01.137
to snoop around
before we showed up.

18:01.137 --> 18:04.586
Well, we did find financial
statements from St. Andrew's,

18:04.586 --> 18:07.758
and it turns out that Anna's
tuition was being paid for

18:07.758 --> 18:10.241
by First Light, which is
a church out of South Carolina.

18:10.241 --> 18:12.724
Yeah, we think that's odd,
and it might be significant.

18:12.724 --> 18:16.034
We also found a message from
Anna on Margaret's laptop.

18:16.034 --> 18:18.241
It said, "I can't talk
right now, but I'm okay."

18:18.241 --> 18:19.448
It was sent
from Molokai.

18:19.448 --> 18:20.862
You guys think
she ran to Molokai

18:20.862 --> 18:22.413
because she knew
someone was after her?

18:22.413 --> 18:25.000
She must have. How quickly
can you guys get there?

18:25.000 --> 18:26.758
HPD can't just show up
unannounced.

18:26.758 --> 18:29.620
That's outside our jurisdiction.
But I'll put in a call.

18:29.620 --> 18:31.034
-Okay.
-Also let you know

18:31.034 --> 18:32.724
when I get the results back
from your ring.

18:32.724 --> 18:34.620
Thanks.
Thanks, Gordie.

18:34.620 --> 18:38.586
Molokai might be out of HPD's
jurisdiction but not ours.

18:38.586 --> 18:40.344
Unfortunately,
Island Hoppers is grounded,

18:40.344 --> 18:43.137
so a chopper's
out of the question.

18:43.137 --> 18:45.344
How about
a speed boat?

18:46.758 --> 18:49.586
Hey,
Rick-boat-Mariana.Hey, Piper.

18:49.586 --> 18:52.172
Sorry. That's what I have you
saved in my phone.

18:52.172 --> 18:53.689
These are my friends --
Wait.

18:53.689 --> 18:55.448
Did I give you
my phone number?

18:55.448 --> 18:57.655
No, but you wanted to,
so I asked around.

18:57.655 --> 18:59.103
Oh. Alright.[ Chuckles ]

18:59.103 --> 19:01.172
Anyways, I'm running late,
but I thought about it,

19:01.172 --> 19:04.379
and I think I will give that
drink at La Mariana a chance.

19:04.379 --> 19:06.206
-I'll see ya.
-Okay. Okay.

19:06.206 --> 19:07.482
-Good to meet you.
-Alright.

19:07.482 --> 19:08.862
-Bye.
-See you later.

19:08.862 --> 19:11.103
Okay. It's not
what it looks like.

19:11.103 --> 19:12.586
So that wasn't flirting?

19:12.586 --> 19:14.655
No. Piper works
on the docks.

19:14.655 --> 19:17.310
And, uh, she's got a gripe
with La Mariana,

19:17.310 --> 19:19.448
so I'm trying to
earn her business back.

19:19.448 --> 19:20.655
It's purely platonic.

19:20.655 --> 19:22.379
Mm-hmm.Mm-hmm.

19:22.379 --> 19:25.482
Wow!
Look at this!

19:25.482 --> 19:26.931
Hey, man,
thanks for the hook-up.

19:26.931 --> 19:28.862
Next flight to Molokai
isn't for four hours,

19:28.862 --> 19:31.689
so getting there in 45 minutes,
that is huge.

19:31.689 --> 19:33.379
With this boat,
more like 20.

19:33.379 --> 19:35.000
Good to know.

19:35.000 --> 19:40.241
♪♪

19:40.241 --> 19:42.034
[ Engines rumble ]

19:43.517 --> 19:44.862
Bon voyage.

19:44.862 --> 19:46.241
Higgins: See ya!

19:46.241 --> 19:56.034
♪♪

19:56.034 --> 19:57.724
[ Grunts ]

19:57.724 --> 20:05.655
♪♪

20:05.655 --> 20:07.379
[ Grunting softly ]

20:07.379 --> 20:10.482
♪♪

20:10.482 --> 20:12.344
Shammy:
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

20:14.413 --> 20:15.689
You need a hand?

20:15.689 --> 20:17.862
No, no.

20:17.862 --> 20:19.965
No, thanks.

20:19.965 --> 20:21.689
This I can do.

20:21.689 --> 20:28.620
♪♪

20:28.620 --> 20:31.000
Okay, now, just like
I showed you, TC.

20:31.000 --> 20:32.931
♪♪

20:32.931 --> 20:34.448
[ TC grunting ]

20:34.448 --> 20:39.344
♪♪

20:39.344 --> 20:42.034
Alright.
There you go.

20:44.965 --> 20:46.206
You okay?

20:46.206 --> 20:47.827
I'm gonna
give it a rest.

20:47.827 --> 20:51.068
Okay, but, dude, you're so much
closer than you think.

20:51.068 --> 20:53.965
You've actually done every part
of it at different times.

20:53.965 --> 20:55.862
TC, you just gotta string it
all together now.

20:55.862 --> 20:57.896
Yeah, I know.
But I'm good for now.

20:57.896 --> 20:59.413
Okay, but it's important

20:59.413 --> 21:01.758
to end every session
on a positive note, right?

21:01.758 --> 21:03.689
Even just
a tiny victory, right?

21:03.689 --> 21:05.275
Shammy.
I said I'm good.

21:05.275 --> 21:07.206
No, but, I mean, even just to
set it up again, right?

21:07.206 --> 21:10.241
Just put the board --Look, I said I'm good, man!

21:10.241 --> 21:11.620
Damn!

21:18.068 --> 21:21.413
[ Exhales sharply ]
It's been a big day.

21:21.413 --> 21:23.413
Uh, why don't we
take a break?

21:23.413 --> 21:28.275
♪♪

21:28.275 --> 21:29.862
Yeah.

21:29.862 --> 21:35.758
♪♪

21:35.758 --> 21:41.482
♪♪

21:41.482 --> 21:43.344
[ Breathes deeply ]

21:43.344 --> 21:50.758
♪♪

21:56.344 --> 21:58.034
[ Engines rumbling ]

21:58.034 --> 22:05.344
♪♪

22:05.344 --> 22:12.379
♪♪

22:12.379 --> 22:14.758
Higgins: Okay, looks like
we're about two miles

22:14.758 --> 22:16.206
from where Anna
sent the message.

22:16.206 --> 22:17.965
We'll literally be
putting ourselves

22:17.965 --> 22:19.931
between a hitman
and his target.

22:19.931 --> 22:22.241
You're saying that
like it's a bad thing.

22:22.241 --> 22:23.551
I'm just saying...

22:23.551 --> 22:25.586
Thinking about
what you said earlier

22:25.586 --> 22:29.413
and how having a baby
would change things for us.

22:29.413 --> 22:30.758
And?
It would.

22:30.758 --> 22:33.206
Gonna have to, you know,

22:33.206 --> 22:35.172
think about being
in dangerous situations.

22:35.172 --> 22:37.310
Not that we wouldn't
take jobs like this,

22:37.310 --> 22:39.379
but it would be a factor.

22:39.379 --> 22:43.172
Yeah. A baby would
definitely change things.

22:43.172 --> 22:46.482
Yeah, well, you know
what's weird, is that...

22:46.482 --> 22:48.448
it doesn't
really scare me.

22:49.551 --> 22:51.103
I don't believe you
for one second.

22:51.103 --> 22:52.620
No, I'm being honest.

22:52.620 --> 22:54.655
Just like when you said
you weren't scared of spiders?

22:54.655 --> 22:56.413
You might be confusing me
with somebody else

22:56.413 --> 22:58.241
because I am not scared
of spiders.

22:58.241 --> 23:00.310
No, I'd be prepared
to deal with a spider

23:00.310 --> 23:02.689
if it jumped on you
or something like that.

23:02.689 --> 23:04.206
That is something
entirely different.

23:04.206 --> 23:06.034
If we had a baby,
I wonder if it would

23:06.034 --> 23:08.862
inherit your gift
of spin.

23:08.862 --> 23:11.551
Or maybe your gift
of sarcasm.

23:11.551 --> 23:14.620
[ Chuckles ][ Cellphone rings ]

23:14.620 --> 23:16.137
Hey, Gordie.
What's up?

23:16.137 --> 23:18.034
The blood on your ring belongs
to a professional hitter

23:18.034 --> 23:20.379
named Clint Watt,
a.k.a. "The Ghost."

23:20.379 --> 23:22.344
The Ghost, huh?
That's a bit of a misnomer.

23:22.344 --> 23:25.103
I mean, you know the guy's
name and profession.
What else you got?

23:25.103 --> 23:26.931
Well, the guy's linked
to at least 27 kills,

23:26.931 --> 23:28.827
and the authorities have never
been able to apprehend him,

23:28.827 --> 23:30.517
so I'd say he's earned
the nickname.

23:30.517 --> 23:33.241
Well, they must have
hired him after Xavier
turned down the job.

23:33.241 --> 23:36.827
Exactly. Now, one of Watt's
aliases recently flew to Oahu.

23:36.827 --> 23:39.034
And the credit card used
to pay for that flight

23:39.034 --> 23:40.758
was also used to buy
a prepaid cellphone

23:40.758 --> 23:42.379
after that flight landed.

23:42.379 --> 23:45.275
And we pinged it,
got a location in Pearl City.

23:45.275 --> 23:48.172
I'm headed over there now
with SWAT. I'll update you soon.

23:48.172 --> 23:50.034
Okay.
Thanks, Gordie.

23:50.034 --> 23:55.137
♪♪

23:55.137 --> 23:56.206
Great. Thanks.

23:56.206 --> 23:57.758
Hey.
Hey.

23:57.758 --> 23:59.517
Just gettin'
some fresh air.

23:59.517 --> 24:02.551
The freshest on Earth.

24:02.551 --> 24:04.827
Look, Millie.
About earlier...

24:04.827 --> 24:07.103
Please.
I've seen way worse.

24:07.103 --> 24:08.931
Yeah, but that's
not usually me.

24:08.931 --> 24:11.103
Especially not
with my friends.

24:11.103 --> 24:13.482
After what you've been through,
it's normal.

24:13.482 --> 24:16.551
And believe it or not,
it's actually a good thing.

24:16.551 --> 24:18.862
So you think
that was good?

24:18.862 --> 24:21.586
You've been bottling up
your frustration.

24:21.586 --> 24:23.965
You're finally
letting some out.

24:23.965 --> 24:27.862
So blowin' up like a volcano
is healthy.

24:27.862 --> 24:31.931
No, but anger's
part of recovery.

24:31.931 --> 24:34.000
It's a good first step.

24:34.000 --> 24:36.379
So, what's
the next step?

24:36.379 --> 24:37.655
The hard part.

24:37.655 --> 24:39.551
You've gotta be honest
with yourself

24:39.551 --> 24:41.724
about why
you're frustrated.

24:41.724 --> 24:49.172
♪♪

24:49.172 --> 24:56.413
♪♪

24:56.413 --> 25:03.758
♪♪

25:03.758 --> 25:06.689
Anna's message came
from here.

25:06.689 --> 25:12.379
♪♪

25:12.379 --> 25:17.862
♪♪

25:17.862 --> 25:20.275
All the windows are boarded up
except that one.

25:20.275 --> 25:22.931
It's 9 feet
off the ground.

25:22.931 --> 25:25.275
That's not a problem.

25:25.275 --> 25:30.413
♪♪

25:30.413 --> 25:31.931
Can I borrow your belt?

25:31.931 --> 25:34.137
[ Gasps ] Ahh.

25:34.137 --> 25:40.448
♪♪

25:40.448 --> 25:42.275
FaceTiming you now.

25:42.275 --> 25:43.620
Alright.

25:43.620 --> 25:53.241
♪♪

25:53.241 --> 25:57.034
Okay. Look. There's a guy doing
something at the counter.

25:57.034 --> 25:58.758
And Anna's sitting
in the other room.

25:58.758 --> 26:00.310
Looks like
just the two of them.

26:00.310 --> 26:02.413
Seems like there are
two entrances to this room.

26:02.413 --> 26:05.655
Can't see that front door
from either of them.

26:05.655 --> 26:07.068
Well, if I'm quiet enough,

26:07.068 --> 26:09.344
I can probably pick their lock
and get in.

26:09.344 --> 26:11.517
[ Gate creaks ]

26:11.517 --> 26:18.551
♪♪

26:18.551 --> 26:20.068
[ Gun cocks ]

26:21.655 --> 26:25.344
Anna?
You're gonna be okay.

26:25.344 --> 26:27.689
I can explain.I certainly hope so.

26:27.689 --> 26:34.689
♪♪

26:34.689 --> 26:36.172
No one's
getting hurt here.

26:36.172 --> 26:38.827
And I'm gonna put
the weapon down.

26:38.827 --> 26:40.655
Just like that?Yeah.

26:40.655 --> 26:45.275
♪♪

26:45.275 --> 26:48.793
Why would I want to shoot
the people I hired?

26:48.793 --> 26:51.034
Xavier?

26:51.034 --> 26:53.965
It's nice to finally
meet you in person.

26:59.034 --> 27:00.586
School just got out.

27:00.586 --> 27:02.862
[ Bell rings ]

27:02.862 --> 27:04.862
I was going to stop by
an ABC Store

27:04.862 --> 27:06.862
on the way to Ms. Neely's.

27:06.862 --> 27:08.517
That'swhen he grabbed me.

27:08.517 --> 27:10.448
[ Tires screech ]

27:10.448 --> 27:13.758
♪♪

27:13.758 --> 27:15.931
[ Muffled screams ]

27:15.931 --> 27:18.034
[ Anna screaming ]

27:18.034 --> 27:19.793
I screamed and screamed.

27:19.793 --> 27:23.448
He said my life was in danger
and he was trying to save me.

27:23.448 --> 27:25.517
Obviously,
I didn't believe him.

27:25.517 --> 27:26.758
Until...

27:26.758 --> 27:28.241
[ Gunfire ]Get down!

27:28.241 --> 27:30.896
♪♪

27:30.896 --> 27:33.241
We barely got away.

27:33.241 --> 27:36.586
And that's when
he took me here.

27:36.586 --> 27:39.103
I have no idea why someone
wants me dead,

27:39.103 --> 27:41.517
but Xavier
definitely saved me.

27:41.517 --> 27:47.344
♪♪

27:47.344 --> 27:49.758
You could have told us
you had Anna when you hired us.

27:49.758 --> 27:51.172
I couldn't tell anyone.

27:51.172 --> 27:52.931
It was the only way
to keep her safe.

27:52.931 --> 27:55.551
That's not the only reason
why you stuck around, is it?

27:55.551 --> 27:57.448
What do you mean?You wanted us to figure out

27:57.448 --> 28:01.000
who put the hit on Anna
so you can take them out.

28:02.310 --> 28:05.241
I can't keep Anna here
forever.

28:05.241 --> 28:08.344
Eliminating the threat is
the only long-term solution.

28:08.344 --> 28:10.793
♪♪

28:10.793 --> 28:12.793
[ Sirens wailing ]

28:12.793 --> 28:20.793
♪♪

28:20.793 --> 28:28.620
♪♪

28:28.620 --> 28:31.379
Your target is Clint Watt.
He's a contract killer.

28:31.379 --> 28:33.241
Likely armed and
most definitely dangerous.

28:33.241 --> 28:35.000
We need
every entrance sealed.

28:35.000 --> 28:36.551
If he's in there,
he's not getting out.

28:36.551 --> 28:37.689
Let's move.

28:37.689 --> 28:38.931
[ Indistinct shouting ]

28:38.931 --> 28:47.862
♪♪

28:47.862 --> 28:49.310
Go, go, go, go, go!

28:49.310 --> 28:50.965
-Clear right!
-Clear left!

28:50.965 --> 28:52.689
-Room clear!
-Room clear!

28:52.689 --> 28:54.724
-Clear!
-Clear!

28:54.724 --> 28:57.724
-I'm good here!
-Sir, we're all clear.

28:57.724 --> 29:01.758
♪♪

29:01.758 --> 29:04.586
Katsumoto:
Watt's rental was empty, and
his burner went off the grid.

29:04.586 --> 29:07.103
We did find his laptop, so we
were able to see his financials.

29:07.103 --> 29:08.448
Higgins: Okay.
What did you find?

29:08.448 --> 29:10.241
A big deposit from
a shell corporation

29:10.241 --> 29:12.827
linked to the J. Lyons Trust
in South Carolina.

29:12.827 --> 29:16.000
The church that paid for Anna's
tuition is in South Carolina.

29:16.000 --> 29:18.068
Yeah, that can't be
a coincidence.

29:18.068 --> 29:19.620
What do we know about
The J. Lyons Trust?

29:19.620 --> 29:21.379
It was started
by Jimmy Lyons,

29:21.379 --> 29:23.862
a wealthy televangelist
who recently passed away.

29:23.862 --> 29:26.620
Left everything to his son,
Jimmy Lyons Jr.

29:26.620 --> 29:28.517
Okay, so some
wealthy TV preacher

29:28.517 --> 29:31.827
is paying the tuition
for this young girl.

29:31.827 --> 29:34.344
That's -- That's worth a deeper
dive, I would say, huh?

29:34.344 --> 29:36.965
Yeah.
I'm already on it.

29:36.965 --> 29:39.517
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:41.931 --> 29:44.379
[ TC grunting ]

29:44.379 --> 29:49.310
♪♪

29:49.310 --> 29:50.758
Whoa!

29:50.758 --> 29:52.655
Well, I'll be!

29:55.310 --> 29:59.827
Yeah, you're only supposed to do
the slow clap in a big group

29:59.827 --> 30:01.793
so that other people
can join in.

30:01.793 --> 30:03.000
You're right.

30:03.000 --> 30:04.586
[ Laughs ]

30:04.586 --> 30:07.034
Hey. So, look. I checked out
the rest of the facility here.

30:07.034 --> 30:08.655
It's all top-notch.

30:08.655 --> 30:10.517
Except the cafeteria.

30:10.517 --> 30:12.482
Kumu and I are thinking about
grabbing some burgers

30:12.482 --> 30:14.586
from Chubbies
and smuggling them in.

30:14.586 --> 30:16.551
What do you think?
You want one?

30:16.551 --> 30:18.034
No.

30:18.034 --> 30:19.896
I want two.

30:19.896 --> 30:21.896
You got it!

30:21.896 --> 30:23.620
Hey, Sham, wait.

30:25.620 --> 30:27.241
About earlier, man...

30:27.241 --> 30:29.137
TC, it's cool.

30:29.137 --> 30:32.413
Yeah, I know.
But I've been thinking.

30:32.413 --> 30:35.620
You having been
through this before

30:35.620 --> 30:38.000
obviously has its pros.

30:38.000 --> 30:41.827
But it might also
have its cons.

30:41.827 --> 30:43.275
Yeah.

30:44.620 --> 30:49.758
The fact that I wound up
in a chair permanently

30:49.758 --> 30:53.000
maybe isn't the best reminder
for you to be around.

30:53.000 --> 30:54.482
N-No, man.

30:54.482 --> 30:58.275
I love your energy.
Your positivity.

30:58.275 --> 31:00.413
I'm just trying
to make sure

31:00.413 --> 31:03.965
you're not seeing my situation
as a do-over.

31:03.965 --> 31:06.862
[ Chuckles ] No.
No, not at all.

31:06.862 --> 31:08.310
You sure?

31:08.310 --> 31:12.068
'Cause the vibe I caught
was more than positivity.

31:12.068 --> 31:13.689
It was...eagerness.

31:13.689 --> 31:16.241
I'm just tryin' to figure out
where that was comin' from.

31:16.241 --> 31:18.896
TC, brother...

31:18.896 --> 31:23.551
I'm eager because I finally get
a chance to pay you back.

31:23.551 --> 31:24.827
For what?

31:24.827 --> 31:27.172
You and Rick
saved my life.

31:27.172 --> 31:28.758
You taught me to fly!

31:28.758 --> 31:31.275
You gave me a job,
a sense of purpose.

31:31.275 --> 31:33.620
I owe you everything, man.

31:34.827 --> 31:36.586
So I figured...

31:36.586 --> 31:40.000
the least I could do
is get you that burger.

31:41.241 --> 31:44.103
You really don't listen,
do you?

31:44.103 --> 31:45.655
I said I want two.

31:45.655 --> 31:47.689
[ Both laugh ]

31:47.689 --> 31:49.206
Two. Two it is.

31:49.206 --> 31:56.931
♪♪

31:56.931 --> 32:01.000
Anna: Wait. That's who's been
paying my tuition?

32:01.000 --> 32:02.689
But why?

32:04.310 --> 32:08.241
Well, it seems like this man,
Jimmy Lyons Sr.,

32:08.241 --> 32:11.448
was on Oahu in 2010,

32:11.448 --> 32:15.344
about, uh, nine months
before you were born.

32:15.344 --> 32:17.689
He...was my dad?

32:20.034 --> 32:22.275
Yeah, it --
it would appear so.

32:22.275 --> 32:30.689
♪♪

32:30.689 --> 32:33.034
Why would Jimmy Jr.
go after Anna

32:33.034 --> 32:35.758
after being able to keep it
a secret for so many years?

32:35.758 --> 32:38.275
The Lyons estate
was recently audited,

32:38.275 --> 32:39.862
so Jimmy Lyons Jr.
just found out

32:39.862 --> 32:41.724
about the payments
doled out for Anna --

32:41.724 --> 32:44.206
first to her mum, and then,
after she passed away,

32:44.206 --> 32:46.793
to St. Andrew's for tuition,
room and board.

32:46.793 --> 32:50.517
But if it comes out that
Anna is Jimmy Sr.'s child

32:50.517 --> 32:52.551
born out of wedlock,
not only would it put

32:52.551 --> 32:54.482
Jimmy Jr.'s entire fortune
in jeopardy

32:54.482 --> 32:58.103
but also the evangelical empire
he inherited, as well.

32:58.103 --> 33:00.689
[ Cellphone rings ]

33:00.689 --> 33:02.793
♪♪

33:02.793 --> 33:04.827
It's Katsumoto again.

33:04.827 --> 33:06.379
Hey. What's up?

33:06.379 --> 33:08.482
Watt's burner briefly
came back on the grid.

33:08.482 --> 33:09.724
He's on Molokai.Where?

33:09.724 --> 33:11.827
I just sent you
his location.

33:14.448 --> 33:16.034
Watt's here!
Everybody get down!

33:16.034 --> 33:17.206
[ Gunshot ][ Grunts ]

33:17.206 --> 33:18.689
-Xavier!
-I'm okay!

33:18.689 --> 33:21.000
Get her behind the fridge!
It's double-paneled steel.

33:21.000 --> 33:23.724
[ Gunshots ]

33:26.241 --> 33:27.620
He's got
some high firepower.

33:27.620 --> 33:29.517
There's more
where that came from.

33:29.517 --> 33:33.344
Local PD is probably
over 20 minutes away!

33:33.344 --> 33:34.724
We're sitting ducks here.

33:34.724 --> 33:36.551
Gotta move. Move!

33:40.413 --> 33:44.241
♪♪

33:44.241 --> 33:46.000
Anna, it's gonna be okay.
Alright?

33:46.000 --> 33:50.000
I just need you to stay calm
and stay down, okay?

33:50.000 --> 33:52.413
He's shooting from coverage.
Makes him a good 70 yards away.

33:52.413 --> 33:53.896
Okay, you brought her here
to keep her safe,

33:53.896 --> 33:55.827
so I'm assuming
you stocked up.

33:55.827 --> 33:58.000
What do you have
that's high-powered?

33:58.000 --> 34:01.000
Tuna. In its mouth.

34:01.000 --> 34:02.482
Okay. Cover me.

34:02.482 --> 34:05.172
[ Gunshots ]

34:05.172 --> 34:11.000
♪♪

34:11.000 --> 34:16.655
♪♪

34:16.655 --> 34:18.068
We're not gonna last
much longer in here.

34:18.068 --> 34:19.688
We don't even know
where he's shooting from.

34:19.688 --> 34:23.137
We gotta figure out some way
to draw him out.

34:23.137 --> 34:24.447
I'll do it.

34:26.068 --> 34:28.620
No.
I'll make a run for it.

34:28.620 --> 34:31.137
He'll start shooting.
You find him, you take him out.

34:31.137 --> 34:32.585
No!

34:35.241 --> 34:36.931
Alright.

34:39.757 --> 34:41.931
I told you I'd keep you safe,
didn't I?

34:48.344 --> 34:49.896
Don't miss.

34:49.896 --> 34:51.310
I won't.

34:51.310 --> 34:57.827
♪♪

34:57.827 --> 35:04.275
♪♪

35:04.275 --> 35:06.068
Xavier!

35:12.172 --> 35:13.896
There.
In the tree. Now.

35:13.896 --> 35:15.689
Magnum:
I don't have the shot.

35:21.241 --> 35:22.827
[ Groans ]

35:22.827 --> 35:27.620
♪♪

35:27.620 --> 35:29.000
Yeah, I see him.

35:36.931 --> 35:42.758
♪♪

35:42.758 --> 35:45.241
It's okay.
It's okay.

35:45.241 --> 35:47.965
It's all over.
It's all over.

35:47.965 --> 35:56.103
♪♪

35:56.103 --> 36:04.310
♪♪

36:04.310 --> 36:12.448
♪♪

36:12.448 --> 36:14.413
[ Groans softly ]

36:19.172 --> 36:20.793
[ Exhales softly ]

36:20.793 --> 36:29.827
♪♪

36:29.827 --> 36:31.344
[ Indistinct conversations ]

36:31.344 --> 36:32.655
Mm.

36:32.655 --> 36:33.758
-Mmm.
-Mmm.

36:33.758 --> 36:35.206
-[ Chuckles ]
-Man.

36:35.206 --> 36:37.103
Mm-hmm.

36:39.310 --> 36:42.620
You can always tell how good a
burger is by how quiet it gets.

36:42.620 --> 36:45.310
Mm-hmm.
Hm.

36:45.310 --> 36:46.793
[ Hums ]

36:47.896 --> 36:51.482
Um, are you doing that,
big guy?

36:51.482 --> 36:53.000
Doing what?

36:54.310 --> 36:55.689
That.

36:59.551 --> 37:02.793
TC! Y-Your toe!

37:02.793 --> 37:05.068
I'm not doing nothin'.

37:06.413 --> 37:08.724
Um, okay.

37:08.724 --> 37:10.793
Involuntary spasms
can happen,

37:10.793 --> 37:12.896
but in your case,
it might be a good sign.

37:12.896 --> 37:14.655
Kumu, pinwheel!
Pinwheel!

37:14.655 --> 37:16.103
Y-- Oh, yeah.

37:16.103 --> 37:23.896
♪♪

37:23.896 --> 37:31.517
♪♪

37:31.517 --> 37:32.965
Anything?

37:34.137 --> 37:35.689
TC?

37:37.689 --> 37:41.206
Okay. It's either
really good or really bad.

37:42.379 --> 37:44.620
It's really,
really good.

37:44.620 --> 37:46.241
[ Kumu laughs ]

37:46.241 --> 37:47.448
I-I feel something.

37:47.448 --> 37:49.275
Oh!
Ohh!

37:49.275 --> 37:51.344
I can feel it.

37:51.344 --> 37:52.827
Shammy: Ohh!

37:52.827 --> 37:54.275
Ohh!

37:54.275 --> 37:56.206
[ Crying ]

37:56.206 --> 37:58.413
Oh, man.

37:58.413 --> 38:00.137
Kumu: Ahh!

38:00.137 --> 38:06.034
♪♪

38:06.034 --> 38:08.689
Reporter: Jimmy Lyons Jr.,
son of the late televangelist

38:08.689 --> 38:10.172
Jimmy Lyons, will be charged

38:10.172 --> 38:12.862
with conspiracy
in a murder-for-hire scheme

38:12.862 --> 38:15.482
that has rocked
the entire Lyons empire.

38:15.482 --> 38:17.551
A church spokesperson
commented today...

38:17.551 --> 38:19.206
[ Indistinct conversations ]

38:19.206 --> 38:20.862
Pretty cool.

38:20.862 --> 38:23.551
So is it like
you remember it?

38:23.551 --> 38:25.000
Not really.

38:25.000 --> 38:26.724
There was a little
more memorabilia

38:26.724 --> 38:28.758
and a lot less of my vomit
on the floor.

38:28.758 --> 38:31.034
Oh. Nice.
Mm-hmm.

38:31.034 --> 38:33.517
In all seriousness,
the place looks great.

38:33.517 --> 38:35.862
Thanks.

38:35.862 --> 38:38.517
So, let me get this straight.
You live on a boat?

38:38.517 --> 38:41.000
Yep.
And you have a job.

38:41.000 --> 38:42.206
Yeah.

38:42.206 --> 38:43.724
And you're single?

38:43.724 --> 38:45.068
Y-Yeah...?

38:45.068 --> 38:46.827
[ Chuckles ]
What was that?

38:46.827 --> 38:48.275
What?
What was what?

38:48.275 --> 38:49.655
You hesitated.No.

38:49.655 --> 38:51.482
Yeah, and then
you drug out your "Y".

38:51.482 --> 38:53.655
You were like,
"Yyyyeah?"

38:53.655 --> 38:55.965
[ Chuckles ] I guess
nothing gets by you.

38:55.965 --> 38:58.241
Um, yes, I am single,
and, uh --

38:58.241 --> 39:03.034
And, uh -- And, yeah, it's --
it's kinda complicated.

39:03.034 --> 39:05.344
Well, maybe
I like complicated.

39:07.551 --> 39:09.241
We should hang out
sometime.

39:09.241 --> 39:10.655
Like, hang out

39:10.655 --> 39:14.206
or, you know, like...
hang out?

39:14.206 --> 39:15.620
Hang out.

39:17.931 --> 39:19.586
Okay.

39:19.586 --> 39:21.206
See you soon, Rick.

39:21.206 --> 39:22.413
Alright.

39:22.413 --> 39:26.206
♪♪

39:26.206 --> 39:27.517
[ Giggles ]

39:27.517 --> 39:36.689
♪♪

39:36.689 --> 39:38.206
Magnum: Just got a text
from Katsumoto.

39:38.206 --> 39:42.896
Looks like Margaret Neely
is conscious and healing up.

39:42.896 --> 39:44.931
Oh, that's great.Yeah.

39:44.931 --> 39:46.931
Oh, and they were able
to identify Xavier.

39:46.931 --> 39:49.034
His real name
is Brent McMichaels.

39:49.034 --> 39:51.793
And he actually didn't have
a criminal record.

39:51.793 --> 39:53.620
They were able
to identify him

39:53.620 --> 39:56.034
because he bounced around foster
care a bunch when he was a kid.

39:56.034 --> 39:59.620
Apparently, he -- he went
through a lot of heavy stuff.

39:59.620 --> 40:03.551
So I wonder if that's why he had
such a soft spot for children,

40:03.551 --> 40:05.758
despite his profession.

40:08.689 --> 40:11.862
Um, speaking of children,
I have news.

40:11.862 --> 40:14.482
Oh, so you're finally
ready to talk.

40:14.482 --> 40:15.689
Okay.
Sorry, sorry.

40:15.689 --> 40:18.103
So, the question is, uh...

40:22.448 --> 40:24.172
Beer
or bottle of water?

40:24.172 --> 40:25.379
[ Chuckles ]

40:25.379 --> 40:28.310
I'm not pregnant.
I'll take a beer.

40:28.310 --> 40:31.206
♪♪

40:31.206 --> 40:32.965
Oh.

40:34.206 --> 40:36.344
"Oh"?

40:36.344 --> 40:37.896
What?
I don't know.

40:37.896 --> 40:40.931
I just kind of thought you'd
be a bit more relieved.

40:40.931 --> 40:44.965
Yeah, yeah. There's --
There's definitely some relief.

40:44.965 --> 40:48.137
Okay. And what if it
had gone the other way?

40:50.689 --> 40:53.655
I think I would've been
intimidated, but...

40:55.310 --> 40:57.620
...but also really happy.

40:59.103 --> 41:02.068
But you're happy that
I'm notpregnant, right?

41:02.068 --> 41:03.862
Yes.
Well, that
doesn't make sense.

41:03.862 --> 41:05.862
No, it makes
perfect sense. Look.

41:05.862 --> 41:07.862
Whatever way this --
this would've turned out,

41:07.862 --> 41:10.172
it would've been
the right way because...

41:12.827 --> 41:15.172
'Cause I...
'Cause I love you.

41:19.758 --> 41:21.448
And you don't have to
say anything.

41:21.448 --> 41:22.862
No, no, no.

41:25.551 --> 41:27.310
I love you, too.

41:28.448 --> 41:32.310
And I think I have
for a really long time.

41:32.310 --> 41:34.689
Okay, well, don't turn it
into a competition.

41:34.689 --> 41:37.655
It's not
who loves who more, okay?

41:37.655 --> 41:39.517
[ Both laugh ]

41:39.517 --> 41:40.965
Well, that's just
as well.

41:40.965 --> 41:44.137
♪ Never gonna let you down ♪

41:44.137 --> 41:46.931
Because you wouldn't
stand a chance.

41:46.931 --> 41:48.482
Hm.
That's what youthink.

41:48.482 --> 41:52.827
♪ I'll be coming home ♪

